                        <condition key="deficient">The Ms. was probably resewn; the sewing is
                           damaged.
 The front board is broken and repaired. 
 Traces of
                           leather are visible on the inner side of the front board; traces of
                           leather or discoloration are visible also on <locus target="#4v">4v</locus> and 123v. 
 The attachment of the front board has been
                           repaired with synthetic threads.
 Quire XI is misplaced, its original
                           position must have been between quires IX and X according to the
                           text.
 Many fols. are affected by humidity.
 Holes or tears
                           amended on fols. 8, 43, 51.</condition>
