               <provenance>The name of the original donor has been
                     erased throughout the Ms. 
 According to Additio 1, the Ms. was donated to
                     the church by ʾabuna Gabra Mikāʾel. His name
                     and the names of his family members are written over erasures in the
                     supplication formulas.
 Besides, the names of ʾArkä Sǝllus and his wife
                     Walatta Māryām, also written over erasures, have been preserved on some fols.
                     (e.g., 38rb, 43vb, 63va, 71ra, 111rb, 113vb) and
                     can be deciphered in Additio 3.</provenance></history>
